A video has been doing the rounds on social media, showing a bridge being swept away by water during what looks like to be a flood. These scenes are said to have been captured in Barberton, which is partially true. This Barberton, however, is on another continent. ALSO READ:Â WATCH: Lowveld National Botanical Garden closed to the public due to storm damage The video presumably shows a river near Barberton, Ohio, USA, approximated to be during 2019, washing a bridge away. Sheryn Nader from Barberton confirmed that the video is most definitely not of a bridge in this South African town. The video was posted on TikTok last year. Lowvelder wants to encourage its readers not to believe everything shared on social media. 